There is a significant price difference between countries, especially for the Pro models. The base storage for the Pro Max has increased to 256GB. A price comparison table shows the prices of the different iPhone models in various countries including India, UK, US, Singapore, Australia, and Vietnam. Additional taxes may be applied in certain regions. Read More Apple has launched the iPhone 15 series with pre-orders starting on September 15 and availability from September 22. There is a significant price difference between countries, especially for the Pro models. The base storage for the Pro Max has increased to 256GB. A price comparison table shows the prices of the different iPhone models in various countries including India, UK, US, Singapore, Australia, and Vietnam. Additional taxes may be applied in certain regions. Apple iPhone 15 series is here and the newly launched iPhones are set to go on pre-orders starting September 15 and will be available starting September 22. The handset was launched in several different regions in phase 1, including India and like every year, there’s a big difference in pricing among countries like India, Hong Kong, Dubai, the US, among others. The price difference between India and other countries is even bigger for the Pro models -- the iPhone 15 Pro and iPhone 15 Pro Max. That said, Apple has launched the iPhone 15 at Rs 5,000 more compared to last year's model and Rs 20,000 more for the iPhone Pro Max. The notable part here is that the Pro Max’s base storage has changed to 256GB from 128GB. So, you’ll be getting almost twice the storage for that added cost. function getCookie(cname) {
  var name = cname + '=';
  var ca = document.cookie.split(';');
  for (var i = 0; i < ca.length; i++) {
    var c = ca[i];
    while (c.charAt(0) == ' ') {
      c = c.substring(1);
    }
    if (c.indexOf(name) == 0) {
      return c.substring(name.length, c.length);
    }
  }
  return '';
}

function handleInterstitial(tmpl) {
  var ref = document.referrer;
  document.cookie="ns=1";
  //In incognito mode, first time there is no cookie and user won't get interstitial, so setting a cookie
  // so that it doesn't return first time in incognito
  //window.location.host.match(/toispadev/) ||
  //(ref.indexOf('google') > -1) ||

  if (
    window.nsShowMaxCount < 1 ||
    window.isPrime ||
    (ref.match(/defaultinterstitial/) && getCookie('nsIstial')) ||
    (ref.match(/defaultinterstitial_indirect/) && getCookie('nsIstial')) ||
    document.cookie === '' ||
    /bot|googlebot|crawler|spider|robot|crawling/i.test(navigator.userAgent)
  ) {
    //toiprops.cookie.remove('nsIstial');
    document.cookie = 'nsIstial=; expires=Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:00 UTC; domain=.indiatimes.com';
    return true;
  }

  var intCookieName = tmpl ? 'nsIstial_Cook_Adex' : 'nsIstial_Cook';
  var goToInterstitialPage = function() {
    var queryParams = window.location.search;
    if(queryParams.indexOf('back=1') == -1){
      var backto = window.location.pathname + queryParams;
      var template = window.location.pathname === '/us'? 'defaultinterstitial_int_us': 'defaultinterstitial';
      template = tmpl || template;
      window.location.replace(
        'https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/' + template + '.cms?b=' + backto
      );
    }
  };
  var getCookieExpireDate = function() {
    var expireAfter = tmpl ? 0.5 : 1;
    var currentDate = new Date();
    var expirationTime = new Date(currentDate.getTime() +  expireAfter * 60 * 60 * 1000);
    var expirationTimeString = expirationTime.toUTCString();
    return "; expires=" + expirationTimeString + "; path=/";
  }
  var cookieExpire = 1 || tmpl ? getCookieExpireDate() : ''
  ;

  var nsShownCount = parseInt(getCookie(intCookieName), 10) || 0;

  // if use has been in the same session and refreshed the page more than 10 times
  // reset the flags
  if (nsShownCount > 10) {
    document.cookie = intCookieName + '=null';
    nsShownCount = 0;
  }

  if (nsShownCount < window.nsShowMaxCount) {
    if (
      !(
        window.location.href.indexOf('order_id') > -1 &&
        localStorage.getItem('toi_subscription')
      )
    ) {
      nsShownCount += 1;
      document.cookie = intCookieName + '=' + nsShownCount + cookieExpire;
      goToInterstitialPage();
    }
  }
  else{
    nsShownCount += 1;
    document.cookie = intCookieName + '=' + nsShownCount + cookieExpire;
  }

  return;
}
